MANULIFE INSURANCE PRODUCTS – FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS

== LIFE INSURANCE ==

Q: What types of life insurance does Manulife offer?
A: Manulife offers Term Life Insurance (10, 20, or 30-year terms), Whole Life Insurance, and Universal Life Insurance. Term Life provides coverage for a specific period, while Whole Life and Universal Life provide lifetime coverage with a cash value component.

Q: What is the minimum coverage amount?
A: The minimum coverage amount for Manulife Life Insurance is HKD 100,000.

Q: Who can apply for life insurance?
A: Individuals aged 18 to 65 can apply for most Manulife life insurance plans. Some plans may have different age requirements.

Q: What documents are needed to apply?
A: To apply for life insurance, you will need a valid HKID or passport, proof of income (for coverage above HKD 2,000,000), and a completed application form. A medical examination may be required depending on the coverage amount and your health history.


== HEALTH INSURANCE ==

Q: What does Manulife Health Insurance cover?
A: Manulife Health Insurance covers hospitalization, surgical expenses, outpatient services, and prescription medications. Plans vary by tier — Basic, Standard, and Premier.

Q: Is there a waiting period?
A: Yes, there is a standard 30-day waiting period for most health insurance plans. Pre-existing conditions may have a 12-month waiting period.

Q: Can I add family members?
A: Yes, Manulife Health Insurance plans allow you to add your spouse and dependent children (up to age 18, or 23 if full-time students).

Q: What is the difference between Basic, Standard, and Premier plans?
A: Basic covers hospitalization and surgery only. Standard adds outpatient visits and prescription coverage. Premier includes all Standard benefits plus dental, vision, and mental health services, as well as worldwide coverage.


== TRAVEL INSURANCE ==

Q: What does Manulife Travel Insurance cover?
A: Coverage includes trip cancellation, medical emergencies abroad, lost baggage, flight delays, and personal liability. Plans are available for single trips or annual multi-trip coverage.

Q: How soon before my trip should I purchase travel insurance?
A: We recommend purchasing travel insurance as soon as you book your trip. Coverage for trip cancellation begins immediately upon purchase.

Q: Does travel insurance cover COVID-19?
A: Yes, Manulife Travel Insurance covers COVID-19-related medical expenses incurred during travel. Trip cancellation due to a positive COVID-19 diagnosis before departure is also covered under eligible plans.

Q: What is the maximum coverage for medical emergencies abroad?
A: Depending on the plan, medical emergency coverage ranges from HKD 500,000 (Basic) to HKD 2,000,000 (Premier) per trip.


== CRITICAL ILLNESS ==

Q: What critical illnesses are covered?
A: Manulife Critical Illness plans cover major conditions including cancer, heart attack, stroke, kidney failure, and major organ transplant — up to 38 critical conditions depending on the plan tier.

Q: What happens when a claim is approved?
A: Upon approval, Manulife pays a lump-sum benefit directly to the policyholder. This amount can be used for any purpose — medical treatment, daily expenses, or recovery support.

Q: Is there an early-stage critical illness benefit?
A: Yes, selected plans offer an early-stage benefit that pays a partial lump sum upon diagnosis of early-stage cancer, early-stage stroke, or minor heart conditions, allowing early access to funds for treatment.

Q: Can I have both critical illness and health insurance?
A: Absolutely. Many Manulife customers hold both. Health insurance covers ongoing medical costs, while critical illness insurance provides a lump-sum payment for financial flexibility during recovery.


== CLAIMS & SERVICE ==

Q: How do I file a claim?
A: You can file a claim through the Manulife mobile app, online at manulife.com.hk, or by visiting any Manulife service center. You will need your policy number and supporting documents.

Q: How long does it take to process a claim?
A: Simple claims are typically processed within 5 business days. Complex claims involving investigations may take up to 30 business days. You can track your claim status through the Manulife app.

Q: How do I contact an advisor?
A: You can request a callback from a Manulife financial advisor through our website, call our hotline at 2510-5600, or visit any Manulife branch.

Q: Can I manage my policy online?
A: Yes, Manulife provides a self-service portal and mobile app where you can view your policy details, download statements, update personal information, submit claims, and request policy changes.

Q: What are Manulife's service center hours?
A: Manulife service centers are open Monday to Friday, 9:00 AM to 5:30 PM, and Saturday, 9:00 AM to 1:00 PM. The phone hotline (2510-5600) is available Monday to Friday, 8:30 AM to 6:00 PM.
